# If your goal is just a simple list
Then this is totally fine as a small wrapper. I’d just rename it and add validation.

Example improved version:

```javascript
class ArrayList {
    #data = [];

    add(item) {
        this.#data.push(item);
        return this;
    }

    remove(index) {
        if (!Number.isInteger(index) || index < 0 || index >= this.#data.length) {
            throw new RangeError("Index out of bounds");
        }
        return this.#data.splice(index, 1)[0];
    }

    get(index) {
        if (!Number.isInteger(index) || index < 0 || index >= this.#data.length) {
            throw new RangeError("Index out of bounds");
        }
        return this.#data[index];
    }

    get size() {
        return this.#data.length;
    }

    isEmpty() {
        return this.#data.length === 0;
    }
}
```

